This is called a method reference; it is useful when you want to use a lambda expression to call an existing method.
Eg. this map operation actually does the following:
.map(new Function<DigitalTwinsResponse<String>, String>() {
        @Override
        public String apply(DigitalTwinsResponse<String> stringDigitalTwinsResponse) {
            return stringDigitalTwinsResponse.getValue();
        }
    });
Since all we do in this anonymous class is call DigitalTwinsResponse.getValue(), we can replace it by a method reference.

